Richard Muponde, Gwanda Correspondent ACCREDITATION for the 21st February Movement celebrations to be held on Saturday has been set for Thursday and Friday in Bulawayo and Matopos. The celebrations will be held at Rhodes Estate Preparatory School in Matobo District, Matabeleland South.The Provincial Administrator for Matabeleland South province, Ms Sthandiwe Ncube, yesterday confirmed the development saying as of now, no one has been accredited. We have not yet started accreditation. It will be held on February 23 and 24 in Bulawayo and at the venue of the celebrations at Reps in Matobo district. For more information, contact the Ministry of Information, Media and Broadcasting Services in Gwanda, said Ms Ncube.Committees tasked with organising the event were yesterday busy on the ground collecting pledges which were made towards the hosting of the event.-@richardmuponde.